21/03/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Bosnian Serb police reported Saturday (20 March) that they are investigating the theft of 125 kilos of explosives and some detonators from a local construction company in Han Derventa, near Pale. A spokesman said there were fears that the material could be used in a terrorist attack.
In other news, police have established that a fire in a Serb church in the village of Cipuljic in the mainly Muslim region of Bugojno was the result of arson. The church sustained minor damage. Borislav Paravac and Sulejman Tihic, the Serb and Muslim members of the country's tripartite presidency, visited the area late Friday. (AFP SRNA, Nezavisne Novine - 20/03/04; AFP - 19/03/04)
